tip.text: Neat place, yummy food! Tried the Ksteak and Eggs, Steroid Burger (in the photo), and Chicken Wings Siracha. No disappointment. Will come back for more. (P.S. The iPad order system is cool!)
Great ambience, awesome jazz renditions (Saturday night), and though the staffs are not the wittiest bunch, they put much effort to deliver service excellence. Kudos! Try the Incredible Foxy!
It's nice and nice only. I really think PdW lacks 'wow' factor it desperately needs. On photo: Choco Monkey Hanito.

formattedAddress: Grand Indonesia, East Mall Level 3A Garden District (Jalan Mohammad Husni Thamrin No. 1)
location.address: Grand Indonesia, East Mall Level 3A Garden District

tip.text: Either you eat their noodles, rice dishes, or simply snacking the dim sums, close the meal with Mango Pudding with Mango Slice! The flavor is genuine!

formattedAddress: Plaza Senayan Arcadia, GF Unit X101-103 (Jalan New Delhi No. 9)
location.address: Plaza Senayan Arcadia, GF Unit X101-103

tip.text: Shockingly satisfying. Crispy Duck Bun (on photo) for starter, Beef Wellington for main course, and Cronut to finish it off. Soothing atmosphere too. Kudos!

formattedAddress: Annex Building, Bakrie Tower (Jl. Epicentrum Tengah)

tip.text: Order the Shen Jiang Bao! Say no more. Never found it elsewhere in Jakarta. Maybe in another fancy Chinese yes, but here the price starts from as cheap as 29,000 IDR for four buns of heaven!

formattedAddress: Gandaria City, Mainstreet GF (Jalan Sultan Iskandar Muda 5/8)

tip.text: I ordered the Donatella Nutella and it tasted just like what I expected of it! A swell combination of orange, chocolate, and vanilla. Gonna come back for the mains in the near future. Great concept!

formattedAddress: Gandaria City G FL Main St. Unit G33 (Jalan Sultan Iskandar Muda)
location.address: Gandaria City G FL Main St. Unit G33

tip.text: Try the Between Love & Hate (Lemon Tart) for your food of choice. As for the coffee, I ordered the Pour Over Djournal Daily and I wasn't disappointed at all. Nice job.

formattedAddress: Grand Indonesia Shopping Town, Pandawa Lobby
location.address: Grand Indonesia Shopping Town, Pandawa Lobby

tip.text: I was amazed. Never thought that light and water with skyscrapers and the bay as the background could deliver a very sweet performance. It's also free! Bravo.
I really think the $33 was worth it. Come early or you'll suffer from the queue. My fav tanks: the Jelly Fish and the Open Sea (the largest one). Please add a shark tank! A bigger and fancier one!
Definitely my fav affordable place to stay in Singapore! Comfy bed and safe storage in the room. Plus: a cozy living room (in the photo). Take away your outside meals and enjoy it there like I did.
They serve halal meatballs now! Don't forget to try their Chicken Wings too; share them if you're not a big eater. For desserts, gotta try the Chocolate and Butterscotch. Great job!
Starbucks Card is here for their 11th anniversary! Can't wait for the integration with Passbook on iOS. Come on, Indonesia!
I prefer the hot Original Chocolate to the "Mayan" one I ordered. She loves her hot Hazelnut White Mocha and macarons.

formattedAddress: Plaza Senayan CP 101B, Palm Gate Entrance (Jalan Asia Afrika No. 8)
location.address: Plaza Senayan CP 101B, Palm Gate Entrance

tip.text: Try the Gindara when you're in need of an alternative dish!

formattedAddress: Kemang Pratama Blok. MM No. 19-20 (Jalan Kemang Pratama Raya)

tip.text: Try the new Chicken Calico set (on the picture)! Enough said. Any other items on the menu is fine, too; but really, try this new stuff.

formattedAddress: Fakultas Ekonomi, Universitas Indonesia (Jl. Lingkar Raya)

tip.text: The food tastes mediocre mostly because it is overpriced; Order the Spaghetti Meatball if you really need to eat. Great music and fast free internet connection. The temperature's hot near the window.
I'm not much of a steak fan, so I'm not qualified enough to talk about the quality of the meat. But yes, the Wagyu was pretty much juicy and tasty. And the Mushroom Sauce? Yum.

formattedAddress: Jl. Boulevard Kelapa Gading WB2 No. 16 (Kelapa Gading)
location.address: Jl. Boulevard Kelapa Gading WB2 No. 16

tip.text: Love the interior! Two thumbs up!

formattedAddress: Jalan Akses UI No. 58 (Kelapa Dua, Cimanggis)

tip.text: I won't talk about the great cityscape scenery or any other stuffs other people commonly said about this place. Just try Bread Butter Pudding and/or Banoffee Pie to close the deal. Yum.

formattedAddress: Menara BCA, Level 56 (Jl. Mohammad Husni Thamrin No. 1)

tip.text: My favourite person's favourite coffee shop. Any coffee on the menu tastes as great. I myself tried the hot chocolate, and it tastes just fine too. Hats off for the ambience.

formattedAddress: Setiabudi One Building Level 1 (Jalan H. R. Rasuna Said Kav. 62)
location.crossStreet: Jalan H. R. Rasuna Said Kav. 62

tip.text: Not the tastiest curry restaurant in town, but cozy enough to spend your time. Try Harajuku Curry like I did. The other items are up to your likings. On the picture: John Dory and Buttered Rice.
Banana Flambe ala Mode for dessert! All other dishes are equally delicious. Love the poetic atmosphere and the actual poem on the wall.
Coconut Pudding for dessert! The Chicken Feet (dimsum) taste great too. Other dishes are equally delicious.

formattedAddress: Gandaria City, Mainstreet GF (Jalan Sultan Iskandar Muda 5/8)
Stasiun Gambir (Jalan Medan Merdeka Timur No. 19-27)

tip.text: The first thing you'll notice: Superfine clove aroma. The house perfectly tells the stories from the very beginning. Don't forget to take a photo at the street stall like I did! Two thumbs up!
When in doubt, order everything.
Ada baiknya dari jip sampai tangga naik kuda. Biar lebih hemat tenaga dan waktu. Plus, naik kuda jg seru kok. Tawar aja.

formattedAddress: Taman Nasional Gunung Bromo (Jalan Cemorolawang - Sukapura)

tip.text: Blueberry Cheese Waffle!
Whatever you eat, don't forget to order the Banana Flambé! Can't get it anywhere else!

formattedAddress: Grand Indonesia Shopping Town, West Mall Lv 5 unit 11 & 11C (Jalan Mohammad Husni Thamrin no. 1)
location.address: Grand Indonesia Shopping Town, West Mall Lv 5 unit 11 & 11C

tip.text: Churros Classic with Cinnamon sprinkles and Seriously Dark Chocolate dip. Nice lighties. Sip a cup of Classic Churreria to seal the deal.
Ada meja lesehan superenak. Yuhu.

formattedAddress: Gedung Sumitro Djojohadikusumo Lt. 1 FEUI (Jalan Lingkar Kampus Raya)

tip.text: Try the Snapper Promo (on the photo: Fried with Herb Rice)! Other favourites: Mozzarella Stick, Carbonara, and Aglio. Drinks: Mojito, Green Lantern, and Dilmah Hot Tea.
It's much more better after the renovation. 3rd Floor for lone study and 4th Floor for discussions. And although I might not utilize it anyway, the 24-hour Studying Room is a definite plus.

formattedAddress: Fak. Ekonomi Universitas Indonesia (Jl. Prof. Dr. Sumitro Djojohadikusumo)

tip.text: An alternative to Chicken Lahar: Chicken Rice Burger. Order the Chicken Karage for your side dish too. Finally, the Ocha Jelly to gulp.
I'm not a regular and I didn't eat the lasagna, but I could really say the Belgian Waffle is delicious as hell. The best. Also the Risotto. And the Carbonara. A tip shouldn't be full of hatred.

formattedAddress: Pacific Place, 4th Floor (Jalan Jenderal Sudirman Kav. 52-53)

tip.text: Try the Chicken Spinach Omelette Muffin accompanied by Earl Grey Iced Tea to start your day! A cozy place to meet up with colleagues. Or not to meet up, and make love with books and/or a Macbook.

formattedAddress: Perpustakaan Pusat UI - Crystal of Knowledge (Universitas Indonesia)
location.address: Perpustakaan Pusat UI - Crystal of Knowledge

tip.text: The best item on the menu (and you can't get it anywhere near too): Chicken Lahar. Try the Green Tea Shake also!
Only got the chance to taste the Strawberry Pannekoek and the standard Dutch Baby, but yes, just as sweet and as yumny as expected. Fair enough!

formattedAddress: Senayan City, LG, Crystal Lagoon (Jalan Asia Afrika Lot 19)

tip.text: Try the Snapper Promo (on the photo: Pan Fried with spinach)! Other favourites: Mozzarella Stick, Carbonara, and Aglio. Drinks: Mojito, Green Lantern, and Dilmah Hot Tea.
Zuppa Soup is good, but their Hutspot met Klapstuk is out of this world; I don't think you can find it anywhere else around here. Nice atmosphere and free wi-fi. Suitable for any occasion.

formattedAddress: Kemang Pratama Blok. MM No. 19-20 (Jalan Kemang Pratama Raya)

tip.text: The Seafood Platter is superb. The best quality and just the right size for tummy. A bit premium, but worth every cents.

formattedAddress: Cilandak Town Square (CITOS), 1st Floor 140-142 (Jalan TB Simatupang Kav. 17)

tip.text: Much kudos for either nigiri or fusion sushi. The bar has the best seats for lone rangers! Plus: A special offer for Danamon card holders. Score.
